# Project Name: SteamClone

## 1. Project Overview
SteamClone is a full-stack web application designed to replicate the core functionality and user experience of the world‚Äôs leading digital game distribution platform, Steam. The project serves as a comprehensive demonstration of modern web development practices, focusing on high-load data management, secure e-commerce transactions, and a social-driven user interface.

The primary objective of this project is to build a scalable ecosystem where users can discover, purchase, and manage a digital library of games, while administrators have the tools to manage the global catalog and user base. built using **Node.js/Express** and **MongoDB**. The primary goal of this application is to provide an intuitive interface for browsing games with advanced filtering (by genre, price, or tags) and a responsive "featured" carousel

Key features:
Secure Transactions: Implementation of a shopping cart system and integrated payment gateways (e.g., PayPal/Stripe) to simulate real-world game purchases.

User Personalization: Creation of persistent user profiles, including a personalized library, "Wishlist" functionality, and purchase history.

Performance & Scalability: Utilization of MongoDB for flexible data modeling of complex game metadata and Redis for caching frequently accessed store pages to optimize load times.

Content Management: A dedicated administrative dashboard to add new titles, manage media assets (trailers/screenshots), and monitor system-wide sales.

## 2. System Architecture
The system follows a standard **Client-Server architecture**.

* **Frontend:** HTML,CSS,JS
* **Backend:** RESTful API built with Node.js and Express.
* **Database:** MongoDB (NoSQL) for flexible schema management.
* **Authentication:** [e.g., OAuth2 / JWT]



## 3. Database Schema Description
The database uses a NoSQL document-based structure. Below are the primary collections:

### Users Collection
Field,Type,Description
_id,ObjectId,Primary Key (Auto-generated by MongoDB)
username,String,The display name of the user
email,String,Unique email address used for login
passwordHash,String,Bcrypt hashed password for security
role,String,"User permissions level (Default: ""user"")"
library,Array (Obj),List of games owned by the user (see sub-fields below)
library.gameId,ObjectId,Reference ID to the Games collection
library.purchaseDate,Date,Timestamp of when the game was acquired
library.hoursPlayed,Number,Total time spent in-game (Default: 0)
createdAt,Date,Timestamp of account creation

### [Example: Products] Collection
Field,Type,Description
_id,ObjectId,Primary Key (Auto-generated by MongoDB)
title,String,The official name of the game
description,String,A detailed summary of the game‚Äôs features and story
price,Number,"The cost of the game in the store (e.g., 59.99)"
genres,Array (String),"Primary categories (e.g., [""Action"", ""RPG""])"
tags,Array (String),"User-defined or descriptive keywords (e.g., ""Open World"", ""Indie"")"
developer,String,The studio that created the game
publisher,String,The company responsible for distributing the game
image,String,URL or file path to the game's cover art/thumbnail
createdAt,Date,Timestamp of when the game was added to the catalog

5. API Documentation

üîê Authentication Module

Handles user registration and session management. | Method | Endpoint | Description | | :--- | :--- | :--- | | POST | /api/auth/register | Create a new user account | | POST | /api/auth/login | Authenticate user and return a JWT token |
üéÆ Games Module

Manages the global game catalog. Supports multi-part form data for image uploads. | Method | Endpoint | Description | | :--- | :--- | :--- | | GET | /api/games | Fetch all games (sorted by newest first) | | GET | /api/games/:id | Fetch detailed information for a specific game | | POST | /api/games | (Admin) Create a new game with image upload | | PUT | /api/games/:id | (Admin) Update game details | | DELETE | /api/games/:id | (Admin) Remove a game from the catalog |
üìö Library Module

Manages the user's personal game collection. Requires authMiddleware. | Method | Endpoint | Description | | :--- | :--- | :--- | | GET | /api/library | Retrieve the authenticated user's game library | | POST | /api/library/add | Add a game to the user's collection | | DELETE | /api/library/remove/:gameId | Remove a game from the user's collection |
üí∞ Order Module

Handles the purchasing logic and financial statistics. | Method | Endpoint | Description | | :--- | :--- | :--- | | POST | /api/orders | Create a new purchase order | | GET | /api/orders/my | Retrieve purchase history for the logged-in user | | GET | /api/orders/revenue | (Admin) Get total revenue and sales statistics |
‚úçÔ∏è Reviews Module

User-generated content and feedback system. | Method | Endpoint | Description | | :--- | :--- | :--- | | POST | /api/reviews | Post a review for a specific game | | GET | /api/reviews/game/:gameId | Get all reviews for a specific game | | GET | /api/reviews/stats/:gameId | Get average rating and review distribution |
üìÅ Media & Uploads

Direct database interaction for file metadata management. | Method | Endpoint | Description | | :--- | :--- | :--- | | POST | /api/upload/upload | Upload a photo and save metadata to photos collection |

